description: This walk follows a pleasant section of the Royal Canal from Enfield to Kilcock in County Meath. The route runs for about 13km along the waterside trail between the two villages. On the way you will pass a series of pretty locks and enjoy some lovely views of the surrounding countryside. You can extend the walk by continuing east to visit Maynooth. The historic Trim Castle is also located just to the north.
